@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
<p class="text-muted">Effective date: March 2026</p>
<hr />

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-9">

        <h5>1. Overview</h5>
        <p>
            InvoiceApp ("we", "our", or "the application") is committed to protecting the privacy and
            security of the data you manage through this platform. This policy explains what data is
            collected, how it is stored, and your rights regarding that data.
        </p>

        <h5>2. Data We Collect</h5>
        <p>When you use InvoiceApp, the following data is stored in our database:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Invoice data</strong> — invoice numbers, issue dates, due dates, payment status, and total amounts</li>
            <li><strong>Client data</strong> — client names, email addresses, phone numbers, and addresses</li>
            <li><strong>Service data</strong> — service names, quantities, unit prices, and calculated totals</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do <strong>not</strong> collect passwords, payment card numbers, or personal authentication credentials.</p>

        <h5>3. How Data Is Used</h5>
        <p>All data entered into InvoiceApp is used solely for the purpose of invoice management within the application. We do not:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Sell or share your data with third parties</li>
            <li>Use your data for advertising or profiling</li>
            <li>Transfer data outside the application without your action</li>
        </ul>

        <h5>4. Data Storage &amp; Security</h5>
        <ul>
            <li>Data is stored in a <strong>PostgreSQL database</strong> hosted on <a href="https://neon.tech" target="_blank">Neon.tech</a> with SSL encryption in transit</li>
            <li>The application is hosted on <a href="https://render.com" target="_blank">Render</a> over HTTPS</li>
            <li>All forms are protected with <strong>Anti-Forgery tokens</strong> to prevent CSRF attacks</li>
            <li>Database access uses <strong>Entity Framework Core</strong> parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection</li>
            <li>Deleted invoices are <strong>soft-deleted</strong> (flagged, not permanently removed) to preserve data integrity</li>
        </ul>

        <h5>5. Data Retention</h5>
        <p>
            Data remains in the system until explicitly deleted by an authorized user.
            Soft-deleted records are retained in the database but hidden from all views.
        </p>

        <h5>6. Your Rights</h5>
        <p>As a user of this application, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>View all data entered into the system</li>
            <li>Edit or correct any invoice, client, or service information</li>
            <li>Delete invoices at any time</li>
        </ul>

        <h5>7. Cookies</h5>
        <p>
            InvoiceApp uses only <strong>session cookies</strong> required for form security (Anti-Forgery) and
            temporary notifications (TempData). No tracking or analytics cookies are used.
        </p>

        <h5>8. Changes to This Policy</h5>
        <p>
            We may update this policy as the application evolves. The effective date at the top of this
            page will reflect the most recent revision.
        </p>

        <h5>9. Contact</h5>
        <p>
            For any questions regarding this privacy policy or your data, please open an issue on the
            <a href="https://github.com/tanhoang0803/InvoiceApp-Invoice-Management-System" target="_blank">GitHub repository</a>.
        </p>

    </div>
</div>
